%N A398080 Decimal expansion of Sum_{k>=1} (zeta(3) - H(2*k,3)) * H(k)/(2*k+1), where H(k) = A001008(k)/A002805(k) is the k-th harmonic number, and H(k,3) = A007408(k)/A007409(k) is the k-th harmonic number of order 3.
%H A398080 Cornel Ioan Vălean, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-031-21262-8">More (Almost) Impossible Integrals, Sums, and Series</a>, Springer Cham, 2023. See section 4.40, p. 437, eq. (4.135), section 5.40, p. 465, section 6.40, pp. 690-694.
%H A398080 <a href="/index/Ha#harmonic">Index entries for sequences related to harmonic numbers</a>.
%F A398080 Equals log(2)^5/15 - log(2)^3*zeta(2)/3 - 7*log(2)^2*zeta(3)/8 + 15*log(2)*zeta(4)/32 - 31*zeta(5)/64 - 7*zeta(2)*zeta(3)/16 + 2*log(2)*Li_4(1/2) + 2*Li_5(1/2).
%e A398080 0.041232806279660023207810779913235512461326027149676...
